,Not Recommended,444350,22815204,"Posted: 5 May, 2016",all,"New Player, Be Nice","My Impression:I love hacking sims and am proficient in real life penetration testing. I own and loved uplink and hacknet (hacknet being the best hacking sim I have played). I went into this with an open mind. This is more of a visual novel than an actual game. There are minigames that are either too easy or make no sense in the context of the game.Positive:+ Achievements+ Steam trading cardsNegatives:- Price for what you are getting, worth $0.99- Minigames that make no sense, dream sequences- Unrealistic environment, most of your time is spent clicking next. The desktop environment is an area clickable region, meaning you can click away from a folder, but it still opens the folder.- You just click buttons like: download, fix virus, etc. Not much thought or gameplay involved.- Story? There really isn't one. It uses buzz words to sound hacker-ish like script kiddie, keylogging, etc- Extremely tedious and boring with unnecessary screen effects- Generic files, fix_it to fix a virus, let's hack a machine and send ourselves money, not realistic at all- Overall, poor execution on every front of a video game: gameplay, sound, graphics, etcBad Game:2/10If you are expecting anything close to real hacking or a game like hacknet, you will be disappointed. Not worth the price, and not even worth the sale unless its $0.99 or less and you are a huge fan of the genre"
