76561198169131721,Not Recommended,444350,22867781,"Posted: 8 May, 2016",all,Maximus Keksimus Meridius,"This is not a hacking game. Its not even a game at all.Edit:I was looking through the reviews and the games I already know (Hacknet, Uplink, etc). I retract myself. This game is not even worth 0.99c. It is not entertaining (I finished it while waiting to find a game in Dota), the story is more generic than a Michael Bay movie, and I've interacted more (and gotten more interested) with a chemistry textbook or Wolfram Alpha. It's like a visual story, without the visual part, or the actual story. The dumb silliness of Goat Simulator or Soda Drinker Pro is better than this.Original review:I know, it's called Hack It. But it's not about hacking. Its about clicking next, doing little puzzles and typing in a console with literally three commands, of which only one matters. The story is not bad, not the greatest either. All in all, the game is a lot more of a visual novel, skipping most of the visual part. If you're looking for a game like Uplink or Hacknet (which is what I was looking for), skip this. But if you're looking for a way to kill an idle afternoon, go for it. The only real downside is the price. $5 was a little too much for my pocket. Maybe if it was $3... Be it as it may, at its current price, and having in mind that it had advertised itself as an Uplink-esque game, I can't recommend it. It's not what I was looking for, and it's not my type of game, but that's up to you."
